<h2>Who can I speak to for more information and advice about PHBs?</h2>
<p>NHS Trafford CCG have a partnership with <a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="https://healthwatchtrafford.co.uk/">Healthwatch Trafford</a> to provide information about Personal Health Budgets. Get in touch via email: <a class="sys_16" href="mailto:info@healthwatchtrafford.co.uk">info@healthwatchtrafford.co.uk</a> or phone: 0300 999 0303. <a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="https://healthwatchtrafford.co.uk/resources/personal-health-budgets-2/">Click here</a> for further information.</p>
<p>For information about advocacy in relation to Personal Health Budgets <a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="https://www.trafforddirectory.co.uk/kb5/trafford/fsd/service.page?id=dX_n-BnOskw">click here.</a>&nbsp; You can also email: <a class="sys_16" href="mailto:admin@advocacyfocus.org.uk">admin@advocacyfocus.org.uk</a> or phone: 0300 323 0965.</p>
<p>You can find out more information by visiting <a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/personal-health-budgets/">NHS England</a>, and to view a selection of patient stories and shared experiences visit the <a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="https://www.youtube.com/user/TheNHSEngland/search?query=personal+health+budget">NHS England YouTube</a> channel.</p>
<p>Please click on the latest&nbsp;<a title="PHB Leaflet" class="sys_21" href="/docs/About-us/PHB-Leaflet.pdf">Personal Health Budget information leaflet</a> for further details.</p>
<h2>What can&rsquo;t it be spent on?</h2>
<p>You cannot spend the money on:</p>
<ul>
<li>Anything illegal</li>
<li>Statutory acute services</li>
<li>Purchasing primary medical services provided by GP&rsquo;s</li>
<li>Covering urgent or emergency treatment or admissions to hospital</li>
<li>Employing people in ways which breach employment regulations</li>
<li>Purchasing goods or services which do not meet agreed outcomes</li>
<li>Health assessments</li>
<li>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) or counselling</li>
</ul>
